law.text:
A Program participant that receives a grant under § 7-1003 of this subtitle shall submit to the Administration a written report annually, which shall include:
The number of riders and drivers participating in the Program;
The amount and source of matching funds used for grants awarded under § 7-1003 of this subtitle;
The nature of cooperative efforts between the Program participant and other government and private-sector entities;
Innovations in risk management for drivers and riders;
If the Program participant charges fees for door-to-door transportation:
The fee schedule used by the Program participant;
The methodology used in establishing the fee schedule; and
The total amount of fees collected by the Program participant;
The amount and source of any revenue, other than fees reported under item (5) of this section, generated by the Program participant in connection with the Program; and
Any other information required by the Administration to evaluate and operate the Program and monitor the use of grant funds awarded to the Program participant.
